title: Aashish Gupta
text: Broadly, my research examines interrelations between health, environment, and social inequality. A related interest is improving the measurement of demographic and development outcomes in low- and middle-income countries. I was awarded a Civil Registration and Vital Statistics Fellowship by the International Union for the Scientific Study of Population, and the Dorothy Thomas Award for best graduate student paper by the Population Association of America in 2021. My research has been published in leading journals such as Population and Development Review, Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, and World Development.

title: Updates
text: August 2023: The call for papers for the 2024 annual meeting of the Population Association of America is out! I am organizing a session on “Environmental influences on mortality and morbidity in low- and middle-income countries”. Please consider submitting!
